# VisionBoard — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values. `.env.local`
# is gitignored. Never commit real keys.
#
# `VITE_*` vars are bundled into the client at build time. They must
# be PUBLIC keys (RevenueCat SDK keys, Supabase anon key, etc.) —
# never put server-side secrets here.
#
# Server-side secrets (FCM service account, Supabase service role key,
# RevenueCat REST API secret, push dispatch secret) are set in the
# Netlify dashboard, NOT in this file.

# ── RevenueCat (client SDK keys — public, embedded in the app) ─────
# Generate in: RevenueCat dashboard → Project Settings → API Keys.
# Use the Public SDK key for each platform, NOT the REST API secret.
# `test_` prefix = sandbox; remove `test_` for production keys.
VITE_REVENUECAT_API_KEY_IOS=
VITE_REVENUECAT_API_KEY_ANDROID=

# ── Supabase (existing — already in your local .env) ───────────────
# These are the anon key and project URL the React client reads.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ── Server-side secrets — DO NOT put here, use Netlify env vars ────
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY              (ai-coach-daily.js)
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY      (push-dispatch.js, revenuecat-webhook.js)
# FCM_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON       (push-dispatch.js)
# FCM_PROJECT_ID                 (push-dispatch.js)
# PUSH_DISPATCH_SECRET           (push-dispatch.js manual-trigger auth)
# REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_AUTH        (revenuecat-webhook.js — set the same
#                                  value in RC dashboard → Integrations
#                                  → Webhooks → Authorization header)
